{%- elsif h == 'property-title' -%}

  <details class="product-faq__item">
    <summary class="product-faq__question">
      <span>What information do title documents include?</span>
      <svg class="product-faq__chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
    </summary>
    <div class="product-faq__answer">
      <p>Title documents show the registered owner, the extent of the property on a plan, any charges or mortgages, rights of way, easements, restrictive covenants, and the class of title held.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="product-faq__item">
    <summary class="product-faq__question">
      <span>How quickly will I receive them?</span>
      <svg class="product-faq__chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
    </summary>
    <div class="product-faq__answer">
      <p>Title documents are typically delivered to your email within 24 hours of placing your order. In most cases they arrive the same working day.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="product-faq__item">
    <summary class="product-faq__question">
      <span>Can I get title documents for any property?</span>
      <svg class="product-faq__chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
    </summary>
    <div class="product-faq__answer">
      <p>We can obtain title documents for any registered property in England & Wales. A small number of older properties remain unregistered — if this is the case, we'll let you know and advise on next steps.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

{%- elsif h == 'rent-increase-service' -%}

  <details class="product-faq__item">
    <summary class="product-faq__question">
      <span>What is a Section 13 notice?</span>
      <svg class="product-faq__chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
    </summary>
    <div class="product-faq__answer">
      <p>A Section 13 notice is the legal mechanism under the Housing Act 1988 for increasing rent on an Assured Shorthold Tenancy. It must be served correctly with the right notice period to be valid.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="product-faq__item">
    <summary class="product-faq__question">
      <span>How much notice do I need to give?</span>
      <svg class="product-faq__chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
    </summary>
    <div class="product-faq__answer">
      <p>For monthly tenancies, you must give at least one month's notice. For yearly tenancies, six months' notice is required. We'll calculate the correct notice period based on your tenancy details.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="product-faq__item">
    <summary class="product-faq__question">
      <span>What if my tenant disputes the increase?</span>
      <svg class="product-faq__chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
    </summary>
    <div class="product-faq__answer">
      <p>If your tenant refers the notice to a First-tier Tribunal, the Tribunal will assess whether the proposed rent is a fair market rate. We support you through this process and ensure your notice is compliant to give you the strongest position.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

{%- elsif h == 'tenancy-agreement' or h == 'tenancy-agreement-digital-signature' -%}

  <details class="product-faq__item">
    <summary class="product-faq__question">
      <span>Is the agreement legally compliant?</span>
      <svg class="product-faq__chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
    </summary>
    <div class="product-faq__answer">
      <p>Yes. All our tenancy agreements are drafted to comply with the latest UK housing legislation, including the Housing Act 1988, Deregulation Act 2015, and Tenant Fees Act 2019.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="product-faq__item">
    <summary class="product-faq__question">
      <span>Can I customise the terms?</span>
      <svg class="product-faq__chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
    </summary>
    <div class="product-faq__answer">
      <p>Absolutely. When you order, you provide your specific details — property address, tenant names, rent amount, deposit, tenancy start date, and any special clauses. We draft the agreement to your exact requirements.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="product-faq__item">
    <summary class="product-faq__question">
      <span>How does digital signing work?</span>
      <svg class="product-faq__chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
    </summary>
    <div class="product-faq__answer">
      <p>Once the agreement is drafted, we send it to all parties via a secure digital signature platform. Each person signs electronically and receives a fully executed PDF copy — no printing or posting required.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="product-faq__item">
    <summary class="product-faq__question">
      <span>Do I need a new agreement for each tenancy?</span>
      <svg class="product-faq__chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
    </summary>
    <div class="product-faq__answer">
      <p>Yes — each new tenancy or renewal should have a fresh agreement. This ensures the terms are up to date with current legislation and protects your ability to serve valid notices if needed.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

